08/04/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The presidential campaign entered its second phase on Wednesday (7 April). 
All four candidates -- Prime Minister and ruling coalition leader Branko Crvenkovski, Sasko Kedev of the main opposition VMRO-DPMNE, the Democratic Union of Integration's Gim Ostreni and the Democratic Party of Albania's Zudi Xhelili -- will take a break from rallies and hold a televised debate. 
The campaign wraps up Monday, with the vote scheduled for Wednesday.
In other news, Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski predicts significant improvement soon in the country's security situation. 
In an interview Wednesday with the British newspaper <I>Jane's Intelligence Review </I>, he noted this is the first year there has been no foreign military presence in Macedonia. 
(Utrinski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 08/04/04; Makfax, A1 TV, AFP - 07/04/04)
